---
title: The devices
description: skyBlip Go, skyBlip Panel, skyPost Helio and skyPost Bridge · the ADS-L devices, in the aircraft and on the ground.
---

<section>
  <h2 class="kicker">In the aircraft</h2>
  <div class="wordmark wordmark-section"><span class="quiet">sky</span><span class="loud">Bl<span class="glyph">&#305;<svg class="overlay overlay-blip" viewBox="0 0 40 40" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="20" cy="34" r="5.5" fill="#FF4F1F"/><path d="M10 25 A14 14 0 0 1 30 25" fill="none" stroke="#FF4F1F" stroke-width="3.5" stroke-linecap="round" opacity=".65"/><path d="M4 15 A22 22 0 0 1 36 15" fill="none" stroke="#FF4F1F" stroke-width="3.5" stroke-linecap="round" opacity=".3"/></svg></span>p</span></div>

  <div class="cards">
    <article class="card">
      <h3>skyBlip Go <span class="tag">the tracker</span></h3>
      <p>
        Portable tracker. ADS-L transmission and reception air-to-air, direct
        FLARM reception, ground-to-air uplink reception, e-paper radar,
        proximity alarms, FLARM NMEA over Bluetooth. Operates standalone.
      </p>
      <p class="note">Reference hardware: LilyGO T-Echo Plus.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>skyBlip Panel <span class="tag">the avionics gateway</span></h3>
      <p>
        Avionics gateway for fixed installation, powered from the aircraft
        bus. ADS-L transmission and reception, uplink reception. Outputs:
        RS-232 (FLARM NMEA or GDL90) to the EFIS, GDL90 over WiFi, FLARM
        NMEA over Bluetooth.
      </p>
      <p class="note">Reference hardware: LilyGO T-Beam Supreme, RS-232 adapter.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <h2 class="kicker">On the ground</h2>
  <div class="wordmark wordmark-section"><span class="quiet">sky</span><span class="loud">P<span class="glyph"><span class="o-ring"></span><svg class="overlay overlay-post" viewBox="-25 -25 50 50" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M-11.8 -18 A21.5 21.5 0 0 1 11.8 -18" fill="none" stroke="#FF4F1F" stroke-width="3.5" stroke-linecap="round" opacity=".65"/><path d="M-15.9 -26 A30.5 30.5 0 0 1 15.9 -26" fill="none" stroke="#FF4F1F" stroke-width="3.5" stroke-linecap="round" opacity=".3"/></svg></span>st</span></div>

  <div class="cards">
    <article class="card">
      <h3>skyPost Helio <span class="tag">the solar station</span></h3>
      <p>
        Autonomous solar-powered ground station in a weatherproof enclosure,
        mast-mounted. ADS-B 1090&nbsp;MHz, ADS-L and FLARM 868&nbsp;MHz
        reception, ADS-L uplink with traffic and weather to the skyBlips in
        coverage.
      </p>
      <p class="note">Reference hardware: LilyGO T-Beam Supreme, 1090 receiver, solar kit.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>skyPost Bridge <span class="tag">for existing stations</span></h3>
      <p>
        Add-on module for an existing receiving station: OGN, PiAware,
        adsb.lol. Relays over ADS-L the traffic the station
        already decodes, without touching existing feeds.
      </p>
      <p class="note">Reference hardware: LilyGO T-Beam Supreme.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <h2 class="kicker">Technical details</h2>
  <h3>Platforms</h3>
  <p>
    Two LilyGO hardware platforms cover all four devices. Few boards, each
    supported completely: firmware, documentation, updates.
  </p>

  <div class="table-scroll">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th></th>
          <th>T-Echo Plus<br>skyBlip Go</th>
          <th>T-Beam Supreme<br>skyBlip Panel &middot; skyPost</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><th>Processor</th><td>Nordic nRF52840 · Cortex-M4F, 64&nbsp;MHz</td><td>Espressif ESP32-S3 · 2&times; Xtensa LX7, 240&nbsp;MHz</td></tr>
        <tr><th>GNSS</th><td>Quectel L76K, PPS</td><td>Quectel L76K or u-blox MAX-M10S, PPS</td></tr>
        <tr><th>868&nbsp;MHz radio</th><td>Semtech SX1262</td><td>Semtech SX1262, 22&nbsp;dBm</td></tr>
        <tr><th>1090&nbsp;MHz reception</th><td>—</td><td>via the 1090 receiver module</td></tr>
        <tr><th>Barometer</th><td>Bosch BME280</td><td>Bosch BME280</td></tr>
        <tr><th>Inertial unit</th><td>Bosch BHI260AP</td><td>QST QMI8658</td></tr>
        <tr><th>Display</th><td>1.54&Prime; e-paper, 200&times;200</td><td>1.3&Prime; OLED, 128&times;64</td></tr>
        <tr><th>Audible alarms</th><td>buzzer + vibration motor</td><td>—</td></tr>
        <tr><th>Bluetooth</th><td>BLE 5.0</td><td>BLE 5.0</td></tr>
        <tr><th>WiFi</th><td>—</td><td>802.11 b/g/n</td></tr>
        <tr><th>USB</th><td>USB-C</td><td>USB-C</td></tr>
        <tr><th>Battery</th><td>2400&nbsp;mAh Li-ion</td><td>18650 Li-ion</td></tr>
        <tr><th>Solar charging</th><td>—</td><td>yes (skyPost Helio)</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

